This README is intended for developers of the packages. It explains how to assemble the build-tool free distribution.

To see README details on the code, go to the /sake or /ssc folders.



== Assembling the Build
No build tools. Hurrah!

To generate a scalacArgs file, use,

find src/main -regex ".+\.scala"

or similar. Cut and copy the list. Add to the top the compile line,

-d . -verbose -toolcp Lib/scalatest_2.11-3.0.0-SNAP2 -optimise

Add to the end the sake we need compiling,

./PackageSake.sake

Bingo. Test with,

scalac @scalacArgs

Run the installation task with,

scala -verbose -toolcp sake -Dsake.runner.home= sake.PackageSake installable



== Testing installed versions
The installed scripts can be pointed at ongoing compiles e.g. the script pointed at a Scala and the target compiled .jar e.g.

SCALA_JAR="/home/rob/Deployed/scala-2.11.4/lib/scala-library.jar"
SSC_JAR="/home/rob/Code/trowel/target/scala-2.11/ssc_2.11-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar"


== Documentation
ssc -title "SSC (and Sake)" -rootdoc src/main/rootdoc.txt  -diagrams doc
